"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166407","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-12-01","<p>I refer the hon. Member for Barnsley Central (Dan Jarvis) to a previous answer of 25 November 2014 to questions 215430, 215431, 215432 and 215433:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=215430" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=215430</a></p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166407/answer",,,,,"216136","2014-12-01T16:24:50.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166407/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166407/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-26","Youth Offending Teams","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what criteria will be used to decide which youth offending team will be assessed as part of the fieldwork for the Youth Offending Team Stock Take announced by the Minister for Prisons, Probation and Rehabilitation on 17 November 2014.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","216228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166408","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-12-01","<p /> <p>Youth Offending Teams (YOTs) play a key part in the youth justice system and the Government recognises their valuable contribution to the recent successes of the system. We want to improve our understanding of how YOTs are operating and how they have evolved in light of the changing circumstances surrounding the delivery of local youth justice services.</p><p> </p><p>The stocktake is being coordinated by policy officials in the Ministry of Justice. They are working closely with the Youth Justice Board to finalise the details of this stocktake, which will establish a clearer picture of how the YOT model is operating nationwide.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166408/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T16:32:45.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166408/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166408/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-26","Youth Offending Teams","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will publish the job titles of each official from his Department with responsibility for carrying out the fieldwork for the Youth Offending Team Stock Take announced by the Minister for Prisons, Probation and Rehabilitation on 17 November 2014.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","216229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166409","Leader of the House","false","2014-12-01","<p>None. Short money is not available to parties whose Members have not taken the Oath.</p><p>However, under a resolution of the House of 8 February 2006, financial assistance is provided to opposition parties represented by Members who have chosen not to take their seats. It is under this resolution that Sinn Fein Members claim expenses in connection with the party's representative business.<br><br>It is the Government's view that this issue of representative money for parties that do not take the Oath is primarily a matter for the House itself to resolve.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Mr William Hague","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166409/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T16:19:46.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166409/answer","Biography information for Lord Hague of Richmond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166409/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2014-11-26","Sinn Fein","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what recent discussions he has had with other parties represented in the House of Commons on the payment of allowances to hon. Members representing Sinn Fein; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Mr Jeffrey M. Donaldson","216085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166410","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-12-01","<p>I have regular discussions with Treasury ministers on these and other matters.</p><p>The failure to pay hydrocarbons oil duty in respect of diesel in Northern Ireland remains an issue, but one that is being addressed by HMRC as the overall percentage tax gap in respect of hydrocarbons oil duties across the UK has been reduced by almost a half between 2005/6 and 20012/13.</p><p>HMRC have had a number of notable successes in Northern Ireland including the uncovering of the largest ever toxic waste dump linked to diesel laundering in the UK on 4 November at Forkhill, when 2,000 litres of illicit fuel were seized.</p><p>HMRC’s joint top priorities in Northern Ireland remain the tackling of fuel and tobacco smuggling, and they work closely with UKBA, the PSNI and An Garda Síochána and other agencies on both sides of the border on these issue.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166410/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T15:30:35.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166410/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166410/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-11-26","Smuggling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with HM Treasury about the effect on tax revenues in Northern Ireland resulting from cross-border smuggling.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Mr Jeffrey M. Donaldson","216226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166411","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-12-02","<p>I last met representatives of the Parades Commission on 29 July 2014. This meeting formed part of my wider consultation on my proposal for a Panel on Parading in North Belfast.</p><p>I have had no discussions with the Commission regarding the ongoing protest parades in this area. These are operational matters for the Commission, acting independently of Government.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166411/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T11:53:31.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166411/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166411/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-11-26","Parades: Belfast","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, when she last met the Parades Commission to discuss the situation at Twaddell Avenue, Belfast.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","216140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166412","Prime Minister","false","2014-12-01","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to my hon. Friend the Member for Stafford (Mr Lefroy) at Prime Minister’s Questions on 19 November 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, columns 271-272.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166412/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:10:09.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166412/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166412/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-11-26","Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what discussions he has had with other world leaders over the increasing threat to freedom of religion for (a) Christians and (b) members of other faith groups.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","216221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166413","Prime Minister","false","2014-12-01","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to him on 9 September 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, column 568W.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166413/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:09:04.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166413/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166413/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-11-26","Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what recent discussions he has had with the First Minister of Wales regarding tackling extremism; and what plans he has to discuss that issue at the next Joint Ministerial Council meeting.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","216010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166414","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>The negotiation phase of the project to find a partner for the Vehicle Certification Agency is drawing to a close. I will make a statement on the outcome in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166414/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T12:06:04.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166414/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166414/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Vehicle Certification Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress his Department has made on finding a private sector partner for the Vehicle Certification Agency.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","216086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166415","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>The Maritime and Coastguard Agency operates two small vessels in Scotland. Neither has been fouled by abandoned or lost fishing gear in the last two years.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166415/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:49:36.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166415/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166415/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Rescue Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many instances affecting HM Coastguard ships there have been of fouling from abandoned or lost fishing gear in the last two years; how many operational days have been lost from (a) ship and (b) personal activities as a result of those instances; and what estimate he has made of the cost of (i) the loss of operational activity and (ii) repairs.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gilbert","St Austell and Newquay","Stephen Gilbert","216043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166416","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-03","<p>The Department is unable to provide information on how much, if anything, has been spent on take-away food for staff as data is not collected at this level of detail and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166416/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T11:03:25.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166416/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166416/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Take-away Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much his Department has spent on take-away food for staff since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","216100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166417","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>The average number of staff working the night shift at the National Maritime Operations Centre (NMOC) in Fareham in the period October to November 2014 was six.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It should be noted that due to the flexibility offered by the new National Network the NMOC and Coastguard Operations Centres (CGOC) do not have fixed geographic boundaries. Workload is managed at the network rather than individual centre level as is the case with Maritime Rescue Coordination Centres (MRCC). Therefore, the operational area the NMOC covered during this period varied:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· From 1 October 2014 to 3 October 2014, the NMOC covered the operational zones relating to the former Solent and Portland MRCC areas of operation;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· From 3 October 2014 to 17 October 2014, the NMOC covered the operational zones relating to the former Solent, Portland and Falmouth areas of operation (the Falmouth CGOC site was undergoing its planned refurbishment); and</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· From 17 October to 31 October, the NMOC covered the operational zones relating to the former Solent and Portland MRCC areas of operation (CGOC Falmouth was operating the operational zones relating to MRCC Falmouth’s former operational area).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166417/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:40:46.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166417/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166417/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","HM Coastguard","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the average number of staff working the night shift at the National Maritime Operations Centre in Fareham was in the period October to November 2014.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","216240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166418","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-03","<p>The table below shows the spend on refreshments by the Department for Transport and its agencies (Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency, Highways Agency, Maritime and Coastguard Agency, Vehicle Certification Agency, Driving Standards Agency, Vehicle and Operator Services Agency).</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td><strong>Department for Transport and Agencies </strong></td></tr><tr><td>2010-11</td><td>11 months from May</td><td>£248,803.09</td></tr><tr><td>2011-12</td><td>12 months</td><td>£181,701.41</td></tr><tr><td>2012-13</td><td>12 months</td><td>£157,981.01</td></tr><tr><td>2013-14</td><td>12 months</td><td>£174,178.93</td></tr><tr><td>2014-15</td><td>7 months to October</td><td>£103,769.57</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><strong>TOTAL </strong></td><td>£866,434.01</td></tr></tbody></table>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166418/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T11:19:46.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166418/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166418/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Catering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much his Department has spent on catering and hospitality since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","216191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166419","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>To support Maritime Rescue Coordination Centres (MRCC) staff to risk assessed watch levels HM Coastguard seeks to have 16 Coastguards available for watchkeeping duties (i.e. those employed at the MRCC excluding of long term sick, maternity leave and officers under training). The following table outlines the number of staff available for watchkeeping duties at each MRCC for November 2014:</p><p><br></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>MRCC</p></td><td><p>Number</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aberdeen</p></td><td><p>18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Belfast</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dover</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Holyhead</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Humber</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Milford Haven</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Shetland</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Stornoway</p></td><td><p>19</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Liverpool</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Swansea</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Thames</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HM Coastguard closely monitor staffing levels and where it encounters difficulty staffing to risk assessed levels, due to leave, sickness and training, senior manager use, when necessary tried and tested mitigation measures to maintain operations:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· the long standing pairing arrangements which enable each MRCC to be connected to at least one other which is available to provide mutual support;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· increased overtime amongst MRCC staff ; and</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· Coastguards on detached duty.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Due to the flexibility offered by the new National Network the NMOC and Coastguard Operations Centres (CGOC) do not have fixed geographic boundaries. Workload is managed at the network rather than individual centre level as is the case with Maritime Rescue Coordination Centres (MRCC). Therefore the number of Coastguards available to support staffing to minimum levels at the NMOC depends on:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· The season (Peak, High, Medium and Low);</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· Whether it is a week day or week end; and</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>· The size of operational area, as one part of the national network, it is responsible for.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of Coastguards required to be available for watch keeping duties to support minimum watch levels at the NMOC for the areas it managed on 1 November 2014 (the former operational areas of Solent and Portland MRCC) was 24.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166419/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:43:29.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166419/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166419/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","HM Coastguard","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many staff must be employed at each maritime reserve co-ordination centre (MRCC) and the National Maritime Operations Centre in order to avoid any shifts falling beneath risk-assessed staffing levels; and how many staff were employed at each MRCC on 1 November 2014.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","216247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166420","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>The grades of the Coastguards employed at the National Maritime Operations Centre are as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>New Coastguard Job Title</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Civil Service Grade</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Maritime Operations Officer</p></td><td><p>Administrative Officer</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Maritime Operations Officer</p></td><td><p>Executive Officer</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Maritime Operations Specialist</p></td><td><p>Higher Executive Officer</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Maritime Operations Controller</p></td><td><p>Senior Executive Officer</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Maritime Operations Commander</p></td><td><p>Grade 7</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166420/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:38:16.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166420/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166420/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","HM Coastguard","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 26 November 2014 to Question 215596, at what grades are the coastguards in place at the National Maritime Operations Centre.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","216245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166421","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>84 Coastguards have left the service on voluntary redundancy as part of the changes to Her Majesty’s Coastguard.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Payments associated with voluntary redundancy are the responsibility of MyCSP and not the Maritime and Coastguard Agency (MCA). The MCA does not have access to records relating to the speed of those payments.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166421/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:35:18.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166421/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166421/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","HM Coastguard","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of coastguards opting for voluntary redundancy as part of the coastguard reform programmes received their redundancy payment within 30 days of leaving the service.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","216246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166422","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>The number of drivers who have had their driving licence revoked or their application for a driving licence refused due to a hypoglycaemic incident in each of the last five years is set out below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of licences refused/ revoked due to hypoglycaemic incident</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2009</strong></p></td><td><p>210</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p>298</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p>703</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p>1,426</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p>1,066</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The increase in the number of driving licences revoked or refused from 2011 results from the introduction of the changes to the minimum health standards for drivers with diabetes.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166422/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T12:10:35.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166422/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166422/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Driving: Diabetes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many drivers have lost their licence due to hypoglycaemic incidents in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","216231"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166423","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>Since 8 September 2014 to date, 29 employees have resigned from the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166423/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T11:05:41.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166423/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166423/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many employees of the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency have resigned since 8 September 2014.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","216232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166424","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-03","<p>We have no current plans to provide funding to improve accessibility at Ledbury station. Last year we asked the rail industry to nominate stations for our Access for All programme but Ledbury was not among the 278 stations put forward.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166424/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T11:08:12.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166424/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166424/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Ledbury Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has to provide funding for disabled access at Ledbury station.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","216153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166425","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>The Department does not hold this detailed information for the Hereford to Paddington line as it is an operational matter for Network Rail. The Hon. Member may wish to write to Network Rail’s CEO at the following address:</p><p>Mark Carne, Chief Executive Network Rail, Kings Place, 90 York Way, London, N1 9AG.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166425/answer",,,,,"216146 ; 216147","2014-12-01T10:47:19.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166425/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166425/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Railways: Hereford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on the causes of recent recurrent signal failures on the Hereford to Paddington line.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","216151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166426","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-03","<p>Under Control Period 4 (2009 - 2014) Network Rail has doubled the Cotswolds line at a cost of £70m. This involved around 20 miles of track re-doubling from east of Charlbury to Ascott-under-Wychwood, and from Moreton-in-Marsh to west of Evesham, as well as upgrading Worcester Foregate Street station with local growth funds. £895m is being invested in the Reading station area to deliver capacity, capability and performance improvements – and this work is now nearing completion.</p><p> </p><p>Further investment is being delivered in Control Period 5 (2014 – 2019). This includes electrification of the Great Western Mainline from London Paddington to Oxford. Network Rail is delivering significant capacity and passenger improvements at Oxford Station and also delivering significant infrastructure works on sections of this line in preparation for the new Intercity Express, Crossrail, and EMU fleets all being introduced over the next 5 years.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166426/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T15:05:10.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166426/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166426/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Railways: Hereford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what investment Network Rail made in the infrastructure on the Hereford to Paddington line in (a) 2012, (b) 2013 and (c) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","216152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166427","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>The Department does not hold the requested information to that level of granularity. For those train operators which operate the Delay Repay compensation scheme, the Department holds the <em>total </em>compensation paid by year, but not by line, nor route, nor journey.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166427/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T10:52:19.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166427/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166427/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Railways: Hereford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much money was paid in compensation to passengers for delayed trains on the Hereford to Paddington line in (a) 2012, (b) 2013 and (c) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","216150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166428","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-03","<p>The Department does not hold the information in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p>Analysis of anticipated demand and capacity is a key part of Network Rail’s planning for the rail network and the recently published Western Route Study provides analysis of much of the route between Hereford and London.</p><p> </p><p>The Western Route Study is available at the following web address:</p><p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p><a href="http://www.networkrail.co.uk/long-term-planning-process/western-route-study/" target="_blank">http://www.networkrail.co.uk/long-term-planning-process/western-route-study/</a></p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166428/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T11:07:24.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166428/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166428/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Railways: Hereford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on the forecast number of passengers that will be carried on the Hereford to Paddington line in 2014.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","216149"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166429","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-03","<p>Although the Department for Transport does hold some information on passengers carried on the Hereford to Paddington Line, this has been provided on a commercially confidential basis so cannot be released. However, station usage statistics published by the Office of Rail Regulation (ORR) show the estimated number of passengers using each station in Great Britain, including Hereford, and can be found at the link below:</p><p><a href="http://orr.gov.uk/statistics/published-stats/station-usage-estimates" target="_blank">http://orr.gov.uk/statistics/published-stats/station-usage-estimates</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166429/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T11:06:35.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166429/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166429/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Railways: Hereford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many passengers were carried on the Hereford to Paddington line in 2013.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","216148"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166430","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>The Department does not hold this detailed information for the Hereford to Paddington line as it is an operational matter for Network Rail. The Hon. Member may wish to write to Network Rail’s CEO at the following address:</p><p>Mark Carne, Chief Executive Network Rail, Kings Place, 90 York Way, London, N1 9AG.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166430/answer",,,,,"216147 ; 216151","2014-12-01T10:47:19.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166430/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166430/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Railways: Hereford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on how many days have there been delays on the Hereford to Paddington line due to signalling failures in each of the last three years; and what the length was of each such delay.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","216146"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166431","Department for Transport","false","2014-12-01","<p>The Department does not hold this detailed information for the Hereford to Paddington line as it is an operational matter for Network Rail. The Hon. Member may wish to write to Network Rail’s CEO at the following address:</p><p>Mark Carne, Chief Executive Network Rail, Kings Place, 90 York Way, London, N1 9AG.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166431/answer",,,,,"216146 ; 216151","2014-12-01T10:47:19.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166431/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166431/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-26","Railways: Hereford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many signalling failures were reported on the Hereford to Paddington line in (a) 2011, (b) 2012, (c) 2013 and (d) 2014 to date.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","216147"
