"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166433","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p /> <p>Currently receipt of Universal Credit provides automatic access to a range of passported benefits, including free school meals, for all those who meet the relevant qualifying criteria. We have been working closely with other Departments to consider how they might continue to deliver these benefits to those getting Universal Credit as it is rolled out. To ensure the benefits continue to be targeted at those who need them most, we have agreed to the introduction of a system of earnings thresholds to enable the continued delivery of passported benefits under Universal Credit.</p><p> </p><p>We are now working with Departments to determine the right earnings thresholds which will be introduced as claimant numbers expand from 2015/16. Decisions on the provision of those benefits, including the eligibility and verification arrangements to confirm entitlement, will remain the responsibility of the Departments that own them. In the case of free school meals this will remain with the Department for Education.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166433/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:45:53.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166433/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166433/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, which families claiming universal credit will be able to claim free school meals when universal credit is fully rolled out.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","216015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166434","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p /> <p>I have had no such discussions with the Association for Project Safety (APS). The Health and Safety Executive, however, has had extensive discussions with APS about proposals to revise the Construction (Design and Management) Regulations 2007 before, during and following its public consultation on these proposals earlier this year.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166434/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:43:43.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166434/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166434/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Construction: Industrial Health and Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions he has had with the Association for Project Safety on revisions to the Construction (Design and Management) Regulations 2007; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Mr Jeffrey M. Donaldson","216012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166435","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p>The department published planning projections of the Universal Credit caseload on Page 30 in the publication 'Universal Credit at Work' published on 22 October 2014. The publication can be found at the below link.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-at-work" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-at-work</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department is not setting targets for numbers in receipt of Universal Credit at various points in time.</p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166435/answer",,,,,"216022 ; 216057 ; 216088","2014-12-01T17:41:35.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166435/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166435/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people he expects to be claiming universal credit by May 2015.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","216021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166436","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p>The department published planning projections of the Universal Credit caseload on Page 30 in the publication 'Universal Credit at Work' published on 22 October 2014. The publication can be found at the below link.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-at-work" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-at-work</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department is not setting targets for numbers in receipt of Universal Credit at various points in time.</p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166436/answer",,,,,"216021 ; 216057 ; 216088","2014-12-01T17:41:35.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166436/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166436/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many families with one person in work will be accessing universal credit by May 2015.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","216022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166437","Cabinet Office","false","2014-12-01","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166437/answer","PQ 216118 ONS 430.pdf","PQ 216118 ONS 430.pdf","ONS Letter to Member - Working after 65","ONS Letter to Member - Working after 65",,"2014-12-01T11:18:20.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166437/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166437/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-26","Older Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people worked after their 65th birthday in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","216118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166438","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-02","<p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) published its first round of thematic work looking at the annuity market in February this year and, based on the findings of this work, launched a Retirement Income Market Study to look at how competition is working for consumers across this market. In light of the pensions reforms announced at Budget in March 2014, the FCA updated the scope of the market study to be more forward looking.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The FCA also decided to conduct a further thematic review into annuities and is expected to publish both the interim findings of the Retirement Income Market Study and the thematic work on annuities before the end of the year.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166438/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T16:50:45.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166438/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166438/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-26","Annuities","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he expects the Financial Conduct Authority to publish its thematic review of the annuity market.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","216117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166439","HM Treasury","false","2014-12-01","<p>The number of households in receipt of Tax Credits for 2012-13 and 2011-12 are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-tax-credits-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-tax-credits-statistics</a>, in the publications ‘Personal tax credits: Finalised award statistics - geographical statistics’ of each tax year. Information for Denbighshire can be found in Table 2 of each publication and information for the Vale of Clwyd can be found in Table 3.</p><p> </p><p>Years prior to 2011-12 are available at <a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20121103084242/http:/www.hmrc.gov.uk/stats/personal-tax-credits/final-award-geog.htm" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20121103084242/http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/stats/personal-tax-credits/final-award-geog.htm</a> and can be found in the publications ‘Child and Working Tax Credits Statistics Finalised annual awards- Geographical analyses’.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs does not record the number of people in receipt of a Tax Credit award as awards are calculated on a household basis and so the figures provided in the referenced publications are the number of households in receipt of Tax Credits. Households are interpreted by HM Revenue and Customs as single or couple claimants, with or without children.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166439/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T15:14:56.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166439/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166439/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-26","Welfare Tax Credits: Denbighshire","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in each ward of (a) the Vale of Clwyd and (b) Denbighshire have received tax credits in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","216067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166440","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p>The department published planning projections of the Universal Credit caseload on Page 30 in the publication 'Universal Credit at Work' published on 22 October 2014. The publication can be found at the below link.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-at-work" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-at-work</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department is not setting targets for numbers in receipt of Universal Credit at various points in time.</p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166440/answer",,,,,"216021 ; 216022 ; 216057","2014-12-01T17:41:35.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166440/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166440/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many families with children he expects to be claiming universal credit by May 2015.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","216088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166441","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-12-16","<p>Due to reforms to local government finance and the local retention of business rates, the amounts of Revenue Support Grant are not comparable over this period. There have also been changes to local authorities’ responsibilities, including changes of responsibilities between different tiers of local government.</p><p>The headline figures for Revenue Support Grant for local authorities are set out in the Local Government Finance report presented to Parliament each year.</p><p>Of course, every bit of the public sector needs to do its bit to pay off the deficit left by the last Labour Government, including local government which accounts for a quarter of all public spending. Notwithstanding, the table below shows local authority total net current expenditure by year, which gives a broader picture of local authority spending as a whole over this period.</p><p><br><em>Local authority net current expenditure (excluding education) in England (£ billions)</em></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2008-09</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009-10</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014-15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£70.9 bn</p></td><td><p>£74.7 bn</p></td><td><p>£76.0 bn</p></td><td><p>£75.0 bn</p></td><td><p>£74.8 bn</p></td><td><p>£77.0 bn</p></td><td><p>£78.9 bn</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><sup>Note: Local government spending on education excluded due to the conversion of schools to academies, which has transferred school funding from Local Education Authorities direct to Academies.</sup></p><p><sup>Sources: Revenue Outturn Summary returns up to 2013-14; Revenue Account Budget returns for 2014-15.</sup></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166441/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-16T16:53:50.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166441/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166441/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-26","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the total and percentage change to the level of rate support grant allocated to each local authority area has been since 2010.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","216068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166442","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p>Estimates of the number and proportion of children in relative low income are published in the National Statistics Households Below Average Income (HBAI) series. This information is captured using the Family Resources Survey (FRS) and has been reported since 1998/99 in the DWP’s Households Below Average Income (HBAI) publication. These estimates are available for each financial year up to 2012/13, the latest period for which estimates are available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Comparable estimates are available for each of the constituent countries of the UK and for English regions. The survey sample sizes for these regions are not sufficiently large to support robust single-year figures, so estimates are provided using three-year averages. The latest estimates are for 2010/11-2012/13.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These estimates can be found at the link below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/households-below-average-income-hbai-199495-to-201213" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/households-below-average-income-hbai-199495-to-201213</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Relevant estimates can be found in the &quot;Supporting Data tables (Microsoft Excel files) WINZIP link. The Excel document is titled &quot;chapter_4ts_risk_hbai14.xls&quot;.</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166442/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T16:17:37.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166442/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166442/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of children living in poverty in each constituent part of the UK; and how many children were living in poverty in each such region in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","216112"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166443","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p /> <p>Since May 2010 expenditure on advertising aimed at reducing benefit fraud has been:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Expenditure for campaigns</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Campaign</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total amount</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>Targeting Benefit Thieves</p></td><td><p>£26,118</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>Targeting Benefit Thieves</p></td><td><p>£82,605</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>none</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>Benefits. Are you doing the right thing? Phase I</p></td><td><p> </p><p>£51,503</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>Benefits: Are you doing the right thing? Phase II</p></td><td><p> </p><p>£555,920</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166443/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:46:18.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166443/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166443/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Social Security Benefits: Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much the Government has spent on advertising aimed at reducing benefit fraud since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","216053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166444","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p>The department published planning projections of the Universal Credit caseload on Page 30 in the publication 'Universal Credit at Work' published on 22 October 2014. The publication can be found at the below link.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-at-work" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-at-work</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department is not setting targets for numbers in receipt of Universal Credit at various points in time.</p><p> </p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166444/answer",,,,,"216021 ; 216022 ; 216088","2014-12-01T17:41:35.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166444/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166444/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of claimants of universal credit on (a) 1 April 2015 and (b) 1 October 2015.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166445","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p>I refer my Rt.Hon. Member to the answer I gave on 20 November 2014 to Question UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-11-17/214804/" target="_blank">214804</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We have already published our response to the Oakley Report and a copy can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/332137/jsa-sanctions-independent-review-government-response.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/332137/jsa-sanctions-independent-review-government-response.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>We have accepted all recommendations made by the Oakley Report and we have already implemented a number of improvements. Our response sets out a number of target completion dates for recommendations made by the Oakley Report.</p><p> </p><p>We will look at the remaining recommendations and will keep the House informed on progress and implementation.</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166445/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T16:11:00.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166445/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166445/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what progress he has made in implementing the recommendation in the Oakley Review that the Department should work with providers to pilot a new approach using warnings and non-financial sanctions following a first failure to comply with conditionality on the Work Programme.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166446","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p /> <p>There are several reasons why a new claim could be outstanding and awaiting a decision. For example, the claimant is waiting to receive or has not yet returned their PIP 2 How your disability affects you form, the claimant is awaiting their assessment appointment date, the DWP have not yet made a decision on the claim, or the claimant has told DWP that they wish to withdraw their claim.</p><p> </p><p>We keep the time taken to process claims under constant review and are absolutely committed to improving performance to ensure that claimants receive high quality, objective and fair decisions. We are already seeing improvements to our processes and outcomes and will continue to work further to reduce processing times and levels of work outstanding.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>By the end of the year we expect that nobody will be waiting longer than 16 weeks for an assessment once we have received a completed ‘How your Disability affects you’ form.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166446/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T17:42:29.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166446/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166446/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Personal Independence Payment: Wirral","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he expects disabled people in Wirral with outstanding applications for personal independence payment to receive a decision on their claim.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","216061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166447","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p /> <p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166447/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T16:00:44.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166447/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166447/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Jobseeker's Allowance: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants of jobseeker's allowance have been issued with a three year benefit sanction in each month since October 2012.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166448","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p>Four months before people reach State Pension age, the Department writes, inviting them to claim their State Pension. An information leaflet about the State Pension is enclosed with that letter; it provides details of how to claim Pension Credit.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The easiest way for customers to claim Pension Credit is by telephone removing the need to complete lengthy application forms; they can also claim Housing Benefit at the same time, and are advised of Pension Credit when they claim their State Pension.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>DWP has also introduced a web-based Pension Credit toolkit at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pension-credit-toolkit" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pension-credit-toolkit</a></p><p> </p><p>Its purpose is to provide customer representative organisations with all the information needed in order to talk to pensioners about Pension Credit and other benefits they may be entitled to such as Attendance Allowance. In partnership with Age UK, local authorities and other groups, a structured campaign was undertaken to create awareness of the Toolkit amongst those who support our customers.</p><p> </p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166448/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T12:48:04.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166448/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166448/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Pensioners: Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department has taken to increase awareness among pensioners of the benefits for which they are eligible.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","216051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166449","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p>The number of people who returned to Jobcentre Plus from the Work Programme in May 2014 is published and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/WorkProg/tabtool.html" target="_blank">http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/WorkProg/tabtool.html</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users is available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information for the remainder of the question is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166449/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T15:57:12.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166449/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166449/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people returned to Job Centre Plus from the Work Programme in May 2014; and how many of those people are (a) in a community work placement, (b) subject to daily signing, (c) receiving intensive support, (d) no longer claiming benefit and (e) in none of those positions.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","216059"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166450","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p /> <p>The Department does not hold this information. Information on applications for Discretionary Housing Payments should be sought from individual local authorities.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166450/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T11:43:44.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166450/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166450/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Housing Benefit: Lancaster","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people have made applications for funding from the Discretionary Housing Fund in Lancaster district since the inception of that fund.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","216127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166451","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p /> <p>The Department does not routinely provide take-away food for its employees and does not have specific accounting information for take-away food expenditure. Consequently it is not possible to provide this information.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166451/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T12:49:15.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166451/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166451/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Take-away Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department has spent on take-away food for staff since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","216102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166452","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-01","<p /> <p> </p><p>The commercial activity is expected to be concluded by the end of December. It is not the Department's intention to disclose commercially sensitive information.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166452/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T15:51:34.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166452/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166452/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 26 November 2014 to Question 215554 when the sourcing activity is likely to be concluded; and whether the information about costs will be available at that time.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","216175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166453","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-02","<p /> <p>Departmental expenditure on Hospitality from the start of the 2010 financial year up to 31<sup>st</sup> October 2014, the latest date for which information is available, is shown in the graph attached. Expenditure on catering is not specifically identified but expenditure on Working Lunches and Refreshments is held and this information is also included in the graph.</p><p> </p><p>Expenditure should be seen in the context of the number of staff employed by the Department, Currently 79,514 (as at 31 October 2014), which works out at a cost per head of £1.45 per year.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166453/answer","Catering & Hospitality May 2010-31 Oct 2014.PDF","Catering & Hospitality May 2010-31 Oct 2014.PDF","Catering & Hospitality May 2010-31 Oct 2014","Catering & Hospitality May 2010-31 Oct 2014",,"2014-12-02T13:10:57.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166453/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166453/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Catering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department has spent on catering and hospitality since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","216193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166454","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-01","<p>The latest figures available from The Royal Society for the Prevention of Accidents are that there were three reported deaths in 2012, and two reported deaths in 2013 of children under the age of three from entanglement in looped blind cords.</p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166454/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T10:08:45.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166454/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166454/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-11-26","Window Blinds: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many children under the age of three died from entanglement in looped blind cords in the UK in (a) 2012 and (b) 2013.","false","Biography information for Gordon Banks","Ochil and South Perthshire","Gordon Banks","216237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166455","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-12-02","<p>The Government received more than 5,000 responses to the consultation which are being considered alongside the review by the Department for Work and Pensions into existing provision. The Government will make a decision based on this analysis in time for the provisional local government finance settlement in December 2014.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166455/answer",,,,,"216294 ; 216295 ; 216330 ; 216331","2014-12-02T16:34:01.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166455/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166455/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-26","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many responses were submitted to his Department's consultation on local welfare provision in 2015-16 (a) in total and (b) from local authorities.","false","Biography information for Mark Field","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","216209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166456","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-12-01","<p>The Government will publish a formal response to the Public Account Committee's consideration of the National Audit Office report; this will be presented to Parliament in due course.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166456/answer",,,,,"216169 ; 216198 ; 216230","2014-12-01T16:31:58.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166456/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166456/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-26","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he plans to take in response to the National Audit Office report, Financial sustainability of local authorities, published on 19 November 2014.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","216238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166457","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-12-02","<p>The Department has not made any assessment of the performance of local welfare assistance schemes which are administered by local authorities. The Department for Work and Pensions published a wide ranging review into existing local welfare provision on 5 November.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166457/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T16:36:40.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166457/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166457/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-26","Welfare Assistance Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the performance of local welfare assistance schemes on preventing and reducing homelessness.","false","Biography information for Mark Field","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","216211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166458","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-12-01","<p>The Government will publish a formal response to the Public Account Committee's consideration of the National Audit Office report; this will be presented to Parliament in due course.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166458/answer",,,,,"216169 ; 216230 ; 216238","2014-12-01T16:31:59.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166458/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166458/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-26","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to paragraph 9 of the summary of the National Audit Office report, Financial sustainability of local authorities, published on 19 November 2014, what assessment he has made of the effect on the ability of local authorities to meet their statutory duties of the reduction in government funding to local authorities between 2010-11 and 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","216198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166459","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-03","<p>It is not possible to identify the number of Army Reserve candidates who withdraw from the process specifically as a result of the time taken to process applications. Candidates withdraw for a variety of reasons, such as changing their minds, taking up other opportunities or failing to be contactable by recruiters. They may also be deferred (such as for medical reasons) or pending (candidates choosing to put their applications on hold) for certain periods and re-enter the process at a later date.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166459/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T17:44:14.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166459/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166459/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-26","Army Reserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the oral Answer of the hon. Member for Canterbury on 24 November 2014, Official Report, column 633, on army reserve, how many people have dropped out of the reserve recruitment process as a result of the time taken to process applications since July 2013.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","216196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166460","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-12-01","<p>For 2014-15 Blackpool Unitary Authority has received £23,000 and Lancashire County Council has received £316,000 from Defra to meet their responsibilities under the Flood and Water Management Act. Additional revenue funding is also provided by the Department for Communities and Local Government for the same purpose, through the local government finance settlement. The funding is not ring-fenced.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166460/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T14:44:42.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166460/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166460/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-26","Floods: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what funding her Department has allocated for implementing the Lancashire and Blackpool local flood risk management strategy; and whether any of that funding is ring-fenced for dredging in West Lancashire constituency.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","216236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166461","Department of Health","false","2014-12-03","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>We have had no such discussions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As the hon. Member will be aware, Health is devolved in Northern Ireland and is the responsibility of the Department of Health, Social Services and Public Safety in the Northern Ireland Executive.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166461/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T17:11:05.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166461/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166461/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-11-26","Musculoskeletal Disorders: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he and officials in his Department have had with the Northern Ireland Department of Health to ensure that patients with rare muscle-wasting conditions have access to new and effective drugs.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","216220"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166462","Department of Health","false","2014-12-03","<p>Research and evidence of best practice in health is shared widely across the United Kingdom. However, as health is a devolved matter Ministers do not routinely discuss health issues with their counterparts.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166462/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T16:49:22.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166462/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166462/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-11-26","Cancer: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with the Minister of Health in the Northern Irish Executive on raising awareness of the signs and symptoms of cancer.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","216217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166463","Department of Health","false","2014-12-03","<p>Research and evidence of best practice in health is shared widely across the United Kingdom. However, as health is a devolved matter Ministers do not routinely discuss health issues with their counterparts.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166463/answer",,,,,"216219","2014-12-03T17:24:26.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166463/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166463/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-11-26","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with the devolved administrations on the future treatment and care of people with cancer.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","216218"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166464","Department of Health","false","2014-12-03","<p>Research and evidence of best practice in health is shared widely across the United Kingdom. However, as health is a devolved matter Ministers do not routinely discuss health issues with their counterparts.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166464/answer",,,,,"216218","2014-12-03T17:24:26.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166464/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166464/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-11-26","Cardiovascular System: Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with his counterparts in the devolved administrations to ensure continual improvement in cardiovascular disease outcomes.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","216219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166465","Home Office","false","2014-12-02","<p>The general policy of the Home Office is not to disclose personal information about another person. This is because we have obligations under the Data Protection Act and in law generally to protect this information.<br><br>The UK has a proud history of granting asylum to those who need our protection and every claim will be considered on its individual merits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166465/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T12:49:42.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166465/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166465/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-11-26","Armed Forces: Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to her oral Answer of 24 November 2014, Official Report, column 628, on Bilateral training programmes (Libya), of the five Libyan service personnel who have been in receipt of military training in the UK and are now being investigated for serious crimes, how many have also claimed political asylum in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","216197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166466","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-12-03","<p>Ministers and officials from my Department and the Department for Communities and Local Government hold regular discussions about a number of issues. These include local welfare provision and my department’s review.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166466/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-03T14:30:49.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166466/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/166466/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-11-26","Welfare Assistance Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether he discussed with the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government the local welfare provision review, published by his Department on 5 November 2014, prior to the publication of that review.","false","Biography information for Mark Field","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","216210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167185","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-02","<p>Women have largely been under-represented in peace-building efforts with only 2.5% of signatories to peace agreements being women. This is unacceptable and more must be done. With this in mind, the UK has been working in Afghanistan, and other post-conflict countries, to improve women’s political participation and their role in building peace.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167185/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T15:49:38.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167185/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167185/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-26","Armed Conflict: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the role played by women in peace-building in (a) Afghanistan and (b) other countries entering a post-conflict period.","false","Biography information for Naomi Long","Belfast East","Naomi Long","906381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167186","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-02","The UK is fully supporting US-led efforts, working with the Egyptians, to bring Israeli and Palestinian leaders back to negotiations aimed at achieving a lasting peace. We are also working with European partners, especially France and Germany, to support that US-led process.","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167186/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T16:08:04.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167186/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167186/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-26","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to help bring Israeli and Palestinian leaders back to peace talks.","false","Biography information for Sir Kevin Barron","Rother Valley","Kevin Barron","906392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167187","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-02","<p>We have serious concerns about the human rights situation in Tibet, particularly the reported restrictions being placed on freedom of expression, association and assembly.</p><p> </p><p>We are troubled by reported episodes of violence during popular protests in Tibet. We believe meaningful dialogue is the best way to address underlying grievances.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167187/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T15:25:14.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167187/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167187/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-26","Tibet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the human rights position in Tibet.","false","Biography information for Norman Baker","Lewes","Norman Baker","906390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167188","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-02","<p>Negotiations to ensure Iran’s nuclear programme is peaceful have been tough, but we have made progress. We believe a deal which addresses our concerns is possible. That is why negotiations were extended until 30 June. We believe the twin track policy of sanctions and negotiations is yielding results.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167188/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T15:29:11.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167188/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167188/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-26","Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the prospects of achieving a comprehensive deal with Iran on nuclear issues.","false","Biography information for John Howell","Henley","John Howell","906389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167189","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-02","<p>We remain deeply concerned by the persecution of Christians and other religious minorities in Pakistan. We continue to raise our human rights concerns with the Pakistan authorities at the highest level.</p><p>I raised this issue with the Pakistani High Commissioner on 28 October, and with the Chief Minister of the Punjab, Mr Shanbaz Sharif, on 26 November.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167189/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T15:24:28.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167189/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167189/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-26","Pakistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with the government of Pakistan on protection of Christians in that country.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","906386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167190","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-02","<p>While attacks by Boko Haram continue across the North East of Nigeria, UK and other international support is assisting the Nigerian authorities to improve the coordination and effectiveness of their security operations. I led the UK delegation to the last meeting of regional Foreign Ministers in Abuja on 3 September where I stressed the importance of regional and international cooperation to help Nigeria end the threat from Boko Haram.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167190/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T15:28:55.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167190/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167190/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-26","Nigeria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of international support for the Nigerian authorities in tackling Boko Haram.","false","Biography information for John Robertson","Glasgow North West","John Robertson","906387"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167191","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-02","This Government is committed to working to increase trade across the Commonwealth. Most recently, the Government has provided financial and public support to the new Commonwealth Enterprise and Investment Council so it can fully establish itself as the leading business representation and trade advocacy organisation in the Commonwealth.","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167191/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T15:17:44.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167191/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167191/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-26","Commonwealth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent steps the Government has taken to promote trade within the Commonwealth.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","906383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167192","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-02","Negotiations to ensure Iran’s nuclear programme is peaceful have been tough, but we have made progress. We believe a deal which addresses our concerns is possible. That is why negotiations were extended until 30 June. We believe the twin track policy of sanctions and negotiations is yielding results.","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167192/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T15:31:21.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167192/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/167192/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-26","Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the prospects of achieving a comprehensive deal with Iran on nuclear issues.","false","Biography information for Mrs Pauline Latham","Mid Derbyshire","Pauline Latham","906391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165867","Attorney General","false","2014-12-02","<p>In line with the requirements of the Greening Government Commitment Targets, the Law Officers’ Departments are taking steps to reduce water consumption and costs. Reductions have been achieved through a range of measures including the introduction of water meters and water flow restrictors to reduce usage in washrooms. Reductions in the size of the estate and in staff numbers have also contributed to the decline in water consumption.</p><p>Against the 2009/10 benchmark of 69,068 cubic metres, consumption was reduced by 40% to 41,164 cubic metres by the end of reporting year 2012/13. Projections for reporting year 2013/14 indicate further improvement.</p><p> </p><p>Specific information on the Law Officers’ Departments consumption of water and any associated expenditure during the last financial year is published in their respective Annual Report and Resource Accounts. These also detail actions undertaken to reduce usage. Copies of these are already available in the Library of the House or can found on the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/</a> website.</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Mr Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165867/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T12:26:18.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165867/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165867/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-11-25","Water","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what steps he is taking to reduce water (a) usage and (b) bills in the Law Officers' Departments; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","215953"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165868","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-12-02","<p>The UK is party to the Convention on the Prevention and Punishment of the Crime of Genocide 1948 which requires that we prevent and punish the crime of genocide in our jurisdiction. We are also party to the Convention Against Torture 1948 which requires us to take measures to prevent torture in our jurisdiction, and to prosecute or extradite individuals who are in the UK, and who are alleged to have committed torture anywhere in the world.</p><p> </p><p>As a State Party to the International Criminal Court Statute (ICC), the UK has also made it a domestic crime to commit any of the crimes in the ICC Statute, including genocide and crimes against humanity. Where such crimes take place in the UK, or are committed by UK nationals, they can be prosecuted before the UK courts.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165868/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T15:35:42.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165868/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165868/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-25","Crimes against Humanity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the UK's responsibilities are in international law to identify, prevent, suppress and punish acts of genocide and crimes against humanity; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","215972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165869","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-02","<p>The Department of Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS), including 9 arm-lengths bodies, has a baseline for water use of 283,495m<sup>3 </sup>across the estate. In April 2014 the Department achieved a 45% reduction compared to the baseline.</p><p> </p><p>One method for reducing water consumption since April 2014 has been to install waterless urinals throughout the building at 1 Victoria Street. In addition to this, BIS has also reduced flush capacity by 3 litres so far in year 2014/15.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is aiming to build on the current reduction by the end of year 2014/15 and we anticipate that the decrease in water usage by BIS will equate to a significant financial saving.</p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165869/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-02T17:35:35.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165869/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165869/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-11-25","Water","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to reduce water (a) usage and (b) bills in his Department; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","215952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165870","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-04","<p>The following tables show the largest increases in bilateral trade (exports + imports) in absolute value and percentage terms for goods.</p><p> </p><p>It is often the case that the largest percentage increases are with the smallest trading partners because of the small value of trade with these countries. In order to not distort the percentage increase data in this way the tables only consider the UK's 50 largest trade in goods partners for 2013 and display the top 10 from those selected countries. Change in value of bilateral trade is measured between the 12 months ending September 2013 and the 12 months ending September 2014.</p><p> </p><p>Trade in goods data has been used in this answer as it contains information on all trade partners whereas total trade data (goods and services) as published by ONS are not available for all trading partners.</p><p> </p><p>A full list of trade values covering over 200 countries can be found on the HMRC Overseas Trade Statistics website (goods only): <a href="https://www.uktradeinfo.com/" target="_blank">https://www.uktradeinfo.com/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3"><p>Table 1 Bilateral trade in goods: (50 largest trading partners only)</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><p>Trading partners with largest percentage increase between 12 months</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><p>ending September 2013 and 12 months ending September 2014</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p>Increase in value (£ million)</p></td><td><p>% increase</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Egypt</p></td><td><p>401</p></td><td><p>25%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South Korea</p></td><td><p>1,642</p></td><td><p>23%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>China</p></td><td><p>6,310</p></td><td><p>1