"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165871","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-12-01","<p>Regulatory guidance will be published once the legislation has been made. There is an expectation that the proceeds of the charge will be donated to good causes and retailers will be required to report centrally on proceeds. As the Climate Change Act 2008 does not include powers for the Government to provide directions concerning the use of the proceeds, neither the legislation nor the regulatory guidance will mandate a particular use of the proceeds.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165871/answer",,,,,,"2014-12-01T13:40:12.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165871/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165871/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-11-25","Plastic Bags","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what guidance her Department plans to publish on the purpose to which proceeds of the single-use plastic bag charge can be put; and when that guidance will be published.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","215978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165872","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-28","<p>Earlier this year, the Chancellor set out plans to make Britain the global centre of financial innovation, benefitting consumers and businesses, including a major programme of work looking at the benefits and risks of digital currencies, and to look into whether they could or should be regulated.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>On 3 November, the Treasury published a Call for Information on digital currencies. This Call for Information asks whether there are currently barriers to digital currency businesses setting up in the UK, and the Government will consider access to UK bank accounts as part of this.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In October, the Financial Conduct Authority launched its Innovation Hub to provide support to innovative businesses. It has identified helping innovators access bank accounts as a key priority.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165872/answer",,,,,"215986","2014-11-28T14:11:53.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165872/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165872/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-25","Bitcoin","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his policy is on attracting companies that develop bitcoin technology to locate in the UK.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","215985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165873","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-02","<p>I understand that the University of Chester is working with local partners and the Higher Education Funding Council for England (HEFCE) with the aim of opening a campus in Shrewsbury which in time, may develop into a higher education institution in its own right.</p><p>I will be happy to have a discussion with my Hon. Friend and the Leader of Shropshire Council about the plans to establish a new university in Shrewsbury.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165873/answer",,,,,"215915 ; 215916","2014-12-02T16:04:49.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165873/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165873/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-11-25","Higher Education: Shrewsbury","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will discuss with the Leader of Shropshire Council the technical and financial assistance that would be required to establish a new university in Shrewsbury.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","215914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165874","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-02","<p>I understand that the University of Chester is working with local partners and the Higher Education Funding Council for England (HEFCE) with the aim of opening a campus in Shrewsbury which in time, may develop into a higher education institution in its own right.</p><p>I will be happy to have a discussion with my Hon. Friend and the Leader of Shropshire Council about the plans to establish a new university in Shrewsbury.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165874/answer",,,,,"215914 ; 215916","2014-12-02T16:04:49.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165874/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165874/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-11-25","Higher Education: Shrewsbury","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the potential for a new university to be established in Shrewsbury.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","215915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165875","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-12-02","<p>I understand that the University of Chester is working with local partners and the Higher Education Funding Council for England (HEFCE) with the aim of opening a campus in Shrewsbury which in time, may develop into a higher education institution in its own right.</p><p>I will be happy to have a discussion with my Hon. Friend and the Leader of Shropshire Council about the plans to establish a new university in Shrewsbury.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165875/answer",,,,,"215914 ; 215915","2014-12-02T16:04:49.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165875/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165875/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-11-25","Higher Education: Shrewsbury","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps the Government is taking to support Shropshire Council's efforts to establish a new university in Shrewsbury.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","215916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165876","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-11-28","<p>When initially estimating the overall budget for the compensation schemes for EU Emission Trading System (EU ETS) and the carbon floor price, a sector level approach was taken using ONS data on electricity consumption to estimate the total coverage and eligibility. At that time, it could not be assessed on a business by business basis.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>To date we have paid £45.7 million to 54 electricity-intensive businesses that operate in international markets to compensate for the indirect costs of the EU ETS.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Of the 54 companies we have also paid £21.9 million to 52 of them for the cost of the carbon price support mechanism.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The average compensation per eligible business to date is therefore approximately £1.25 million. However, there is considerable variance in the size of payments.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In any given calendar or financial year from 2016 to 2020 the level of compensation is estimated to be:</p><p> </p><p>a) circa £20 million for EU ETS;</p><p> </p><p>b) circa £70 million for carbon price support.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The overall cost of EU ETS compensation in the future depends on a number of variables including the EU carbon price, which will vary from year to year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165876/answer",,,,,"215933 ; 215934","2014-11-28T14:19:36.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165876/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/165876/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-11-25","Environment Protection: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the number of businesses eligible for compensation for the indirect costs of (a) the EU Emissions Trading System and (b) the carbon price floor.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","215932"
